{0 day11}

An OCaml package build and documentation system. Builds opam packages
in layered overlayfs containers, generates documentation with odoc,
and manages a content-addressed layer cache.

{1 Architecture}

The libraries are organised in layers of increasing domain specificity.

{2 Foundation}

Generic primitives with no domain knowledge:

- {!page-solution} — Solution types: dependency graphs, solve results
- {!page-sys} — Process execution: sudo, locking, fork helper
- {!page-lib} — Shared utilities: logging, progress, GC, notifications

{2 Storage and Runtime}

Layered storage and OCI container execution:

- {!page-layer} — On-disk layer format, overlayfs stacking, LRU, hashing
- {!page-container} — OCI runtime: overlayfs mounts, runc, spec generation
- {!page-runner} — Intersection of layer + container: run commands in layered rootfs

{2 Opam Integration}

Package metadata, solver, and build orchestration:

- {!page-opam} — Git-backed opam package index, environment, dep extraction
- {!page-solver} — Dependency solving via opam-0install
- {!page-solver_pool} — Parallel out-of-process solving
- {!page-opam_layer} — Opam-flavoured layer types: build nodes, tools, sidecars
- {!page-opam_build} — Build orchestration: DAG execution, hash caching, tools

{2 Documentation Pipeline}

Odoc documentation generation:

- {!page-doc} — Full doc pipeline: compile, link, odoc store, metadata, tool management

{2 Batch and Extras}

- {!page-batch} — Batch orchestration: targets, incremental solving, blessing
- {!page-jtw} — JavaScript-to-Wasm build pipeline
- {!page-test_util} — Shared test helpers
